<p>Lark Hill.<br/>This is a succession of English and Australian and New Zealand Camps altogether and are situated in one of the prettiest and healthiest spots in England. It would be impossible to thoroughly describe the Camp as we only drove through it and stayed where the 36th Battalion were quartered but saw a good deal of it in the few hours we were there. Considering that the whole camps are capable of quartering over a million and a quarter troops some idea of the size may be gathered from this. The ride here from Parkhouse to the Camps is through some of the prettiest scenery about here and the majority of the roads are asphalt. There is an ample supply of water laid on all through the camps and the whole is lighted by electricity from several</p>
